going to necessarily tell you

00:51:06.810 --> 00:51:10.110
when they sell the stock
that they told you to buy.

00:51:10.110 --> 00:51:15.140
And also, we talked
about the discomfort

00:51:15.140 --> 00:51:17.030
of owning stocks that go down.

00:51:17.030 --> 00:51:20.390
And generally, I want
to only buy a stock

00:51:20.390 --> 00:51:24.690
where I am excited
if it goes down 50%,

00:51:24.690 --> 00:51:26.640
because then I
can buy even more.

00:51:29.330 --> 00:51:32.580
And if you have
that mindset, you're

00:51:32.580 --> 00:51:34.280
going to be a lot pickier.

00:51:34.280 --> 00:51:37.360
Because usually when
a stock goes down 50%,

00:51:37.360 --> 00:51:39.070
you're really scared.

00:51:39.070 --> 00:51:42.300
You're thinking this
is going to zero.

00:51:42.300 --> 00:51:52.380
So you need to just know what
you think a company's worth,

00:51:52.380 --> 00:51:54.205
and then be comfortable
with the downside.

00:51:55.460 --> 00:51:59.780
So you really need to do
your own work, would be my--

