00:52:14.070 --> 00:52:15.390
and there's no revenue?

00:52:15.390 --> 00:52:16.890
JOHN MIHALJEVIC:
Yeah, that's right.

00:52:16.890 --> 00:52:20.550
And a biotech company
could be worth a lot,

00:52:20.550 --> 00:52:23.320
even if it has no
revenue, but that's

00:52:23.320 --> 00:52:25.900
beyond my capacity to judge.

00:52:25.900 --> 00:52:29.870
And Warren Buffett
once said, you

00:52:29.870 --> 00:52:31.676
need to know your
circle of competence.

00:52:32.920 --> 00:52:36.180
But what's even more important
is to stay within it.

00:52:36.180 --> 00:52:40.140
So it can be small, but
if you stay within that,

00:52:40.140 --> 00:52:41.190
you'll do well.

00:52:41.190 --> 00:52:42.760
And if you venture
outside of it,

00:52:42.760 --> 00:52:46.140
like would be my case
with a biotech company,

00:52:46.140 --> 00:52:49.610
or many other companies--
and it's OK to say,

00:52:49.610 --> 00:52:51.260
I don't know enough.

00:52:51.260 --> 00:52:53.710
Actually, that's what I
would say with most companies

00:52:53.710 --> 00:52:54.600
in the stock market.

00:52:56.830 --> 00:52:59.410
To use a baseball analogy
again from Buffett,

00:52:59.410 --> 00:53:01.990
it's a no-strike called game.

00:53:01.990 --> 00:53:06.820
So you don't need to swing at
every idea that comes your way.

00:53:08.120 --> 00:53:11.440
The only thing that matters
is the companies that you do

00:53:11.440 --> 00:53:14.420
buy, you're right on.

00:53:14.420 --> 00:53:16.980
And even there, you're not
going to be right on every one.

00:53:19.050 --> 00:53:22.210
So stay within your
circle of competence

00:53:22.210 --> 00:53:26.450
and you'll do much better than
if you venture outside of that.

